tip.text: Breakfast set. Done. Feel guilty as you eat that sweet but high caloried combo of jam and butter toast.

tip.text: Comfortable open cafe located on the 2nd floor. Delicious grass jelly drinks. I recommend the hot grass jelly herbal soup, esp on a cold day.
Beef noodles. Get the beef noodles like their name suggests. Get some stewed meats from the self serve counter and enjoy.
The layout of the space could use a little work, but still nice to sip on some delicious tea and browse the beautiful teaware.

tip.text: Adorable open air cafe. Their winter mulled wine is perfect on a cold rainy day. Coffees are good. I'd skip their desserts.

tip.text: Free tasting of their popovers with lemon curd sauce, almond cookie, and tea. Cute little shop with really friendly and passionate shopkeeper. Hard to not give in and buy one of their tasty snacks!

tip.text: Adorable space, calm atmosphere. Definitely a good spot to work or have good conversations. Cakes are delicious too.

Small but serene beach. Head to the nearby Sheer Rocks bar for a cocktail during sunset.

tip.text: Love this place! Highly recommend seafood risotto, mushroom pappardelle and octopus appetizer. Also have Lambrusco by the bottle!

tip.text: Of course the sisig but I also highly recommend the pork jowl with fried brussels sprouts.

tip.text: The Salty Plum Old Fashioned is yum, and the bacon buns are just enough to hold you over before dinner.

tip.text: My favorite croissants ever! Must must have! And definitely the mocha coffee as well. Heaven.

Cocktails in plastic bags? $4 beers, $5 wines, $6 cocktails, and $1 oysters/wings. Not complaining when the HH is fantastic.

Clean, friendly, and new massage chairs! Gel manicures are a must.
Yummy bubble tea drinks and dumplings. My fave is Lavender Matcha or Taro milk tea!
Channel the 75yo in you. Play Uno or other games if you get tired of shuffling. Buy a pizza pie to share from the corner pizza stand.

tip.text: Delicious iced coffee! A little oasis on Flinders.

Fresh seafood for a decent price. $27 for a seafood combo pack that feeds two. Tiny portion of tartar sauce though.
